# Docker build-context excludes for the repo root.
#
# Every v3 service builds with `context: .` and `dockerfile: services/<svc>/Dockerfile`
# (see docker-compose.yml), so this is the single .dockerignore that governs all four
# image builds. Anything matched here never reaches the daemon, so it can't bloat
# layers or leak into images.

# ---- Git + version control --------------------------------------------
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github/

# ---- Python bytecode + virtualenv + sdist metadata --------------------
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/.venv/
**/*.egg-info/

# Defensive `**/` — current tree has only top-level cache dirs, but
# `cd services/backend && uv run pytest` will plant nested ones.
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.coverage
**/.coverage.*
**/htmlcov/

# ---- Node + Vite ------------------------------------------------------
**/node_modules/
# Host-side `npm run build` output — the UI Dockerfile rebuilds inside
# the container, so any pre-existing dist/ is stale noise.
**/dist/
**/.vite/
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# ---- Environment / secrets -------------------------------------------
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Stray key/cert material — defense in depth. No v3 image bakes certs in;
# they are always bind-mounted at runtime. See docs/arch/06-deployment.md.
**/*.key
**/*.pem
**/*.crt
**/*.srl
**/*.p12
**/*.pfx

# ---- Persistent host state (compose bind-mounts these at runtime) ----
certs/
db/
raw/
media/
logs/

# ---- Repo metadata never read inside an image ------------------------
docs/
test_fixtures/
devtools/
install.sh
docker-compose*.yml
.pre-commit-config.yaml
.editorconfig
# Claude Code memory + settings and the GitHub wiki mirror — pure repo
# metadata, tracked in git but never copied into any image.
.claude/
arm_wiki/
# Repo-root favicon is decoration; the UI image ships its own assets and
# no build COPYs this.
favicon.ico

# ---- Test suites -----------------------------------------------------
# Runtime images don't run tests. Vite's build only pulls files reachable
# from main.ts so excluding spec dirs from the UI context is pure
# context-shrink (the runtime nginx image wouldn't have seen them anyway).
**/tests/
**/__tests__/

# ---- Markdown docs (not referenced by any build step) ----------------
**/README.md
**/CHANGELOG.md
**/CONTRIBUTING.md
**/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
**/SECURITY.md
**/CLAUDE.md
# LICENSE is intentionally NOT ignored — it stays in the context so a
# `COPY LICENSE` can bundle it into each image.

# ---- IDE / editor / OS noise -----------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
**/*.swp
**/*.bak
**/*.orig
**/*~
